          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>Click on Add.</para>

    <para>Your search criteria is then added to the list of criterias.</para>

    <para>The fields associated with items (or copies) </para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Location</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Section</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Owner</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Media type</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>operate differently and display a list to choose from. To choose two
    or more values simultaneously, hold down Ctrl key and click on the values
    required.</para>

    <para>For each criteria, enter one or more words or search expressions.
    Then choose where to find the word or words to search for within the field
    using the list box :</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>contains at least one of the words</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>contains all the words</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>starts with</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>ends with</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>exactly like</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>The ISBN field accepts only "starts with" ; fields associated with
    copies of works require only choosing from the list.</para>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Combined search criteria</title>

    <para>For every additional criteria, you need to determine the association
    with the various criterias : and/or/not.</para>

    <para>Criterias add with one another in inverted order : the first
    criteria chosen will be applied last.</para>

    <para>You may specify two conditions for one and same criteria, for
    example, Title starts with.... and Title contains the words...</para>
  </section>
